  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240ºC/ 220ºC (fan)/ gas 9 and boil a kettle</p><p>Trim the green stalk[s] off your <strong>aubergine[s]</strong> and discard, then chop into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Top, tail and chop your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> into quarters lengthways, then chop into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and finely dice <strong>half</strong> your<strong> red onion[s]</strong> and cut the <strong>remaining onion</strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1693573755362-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1693573755362-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1693573755362-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1693573755362-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1693573755362-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped aubergine</strong>, <strong>courgette</strong> and <strong>red onion wedges</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 15 min or until softened and slightly charred</p><p>While the vegetables are in the oven, peel and finely chop your<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1693573759402-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1693573759402-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1693573759402-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1693573759402-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1693573759402-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a medium heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until slightly softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
